[[File:Battledroids_BF.jpg|thumb|250px|[[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]] [[B1-series battle droid/Legends|B1-series battle droid]], [[B2-series super battle droid/Legends|B2 super battle droid]], and [[Droideka/Legends|droideka]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].]]
A '''battle droid''' (also referred to as '''war droid''', '''combat droid''', '''battle bot''', '''killer droid''') was any [[Droid/Legends|droid]] designed for combat. They could typically be found in the service of some galactic [[Politics/Legends|governments]], criminal organizations, and some [[Law enforcement agency/Legends|law enforcement agencies]].

Droids intended solely for combat were relatively rare, and illegal in the post-Ruusan Reformation [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].<ref name="RPG">[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game (first edition)|''Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game'']]</ref>

There were numerous types of battle droids. They predated the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] by thousands of years, with the earliest known being [[Rakatan guardian droid]]s and the [[war-robot]]s used by [[Xim/Legends|Xim the Despot]].

The [[Eternal Empire]] used battle droids known as [[Skytrooper]]s as their primary infantry units.

Many of the best-known battle droids were those used by the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].

At the end of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] turned off the [[Master control signal]], deactivating most of the [[Separatist Droid Army/Legends|Separatist Droid Army]]. After this, battle droids were extremely rare.

Most droids, especially those manufactured in overwhelming numbers, possessed little critical thinking ability and low levels of intelligence, often due to the expensive nature of advanced programming. Several classes of battle droids, however, had higher levels of intelligence; these droids were much more expensive to make, due to their advanced [[Droid brain/Legends|brains]], so therefore were made in smaller quantities. Examples are the [[BX-series droid commando/Legends|BX-series droid commando]], the [[IG-100 MagnaGuard/Legends|IG-100 MagnaGuard]] and, save for the first versions, the [[Droideka/Legends|Droideka]].

